Remarks:
Injection deviation investigation over pump phasing
Use CB08 (2 lobes) for 3 cylinder engine application.                                                                         1) In this application, the max inj-q difference is about 2.5 mm^/str, which is happened at full load point. The difference of injection pressure correspondingly is about 74 bar.

QB calculation
“CB08_1600bar*0.87” - “QErfSys” > 0. Min safe margin is about 2.6 l/h

Start ability test 
With the use of EKP in CB08, the start ability of CB08 is comparable with CB18 in normal condition(40deg, 0m altitude).

CB08 is able to build up rail pressure to 120bar in 1s with pump speed of only 35prpm because of the EKP supplies constant pressure no matter how much the engine speed is.

With pump speed higher than 50prpm, CB08 is able to build up pressure to 120bar in about 0.5s.

Start ability of CB08 is estimated not so much influenced by high temperature and high altitude condition because of the use of EKP. Its flow rate is much higher than flow rate of VP and can be kept constant at start. But it will be checked again in further tests.

Start ability test (Empty tank start)
1.Experiment is done with three different LPC layout methods: EKP in tank, EKP before filter and EKP after filter.
2.Experiment results are quite positive, with Rainbow EKP, system is able to start around 1 second. Because of the utilization of EKP, system deflation capability is out of a problem.
3.In system layout when EKP is after filter, air deflation after empty tank consumes 40 seconds in experiment. When low pressure pipe is very long, restart of engine should wait long engine after switching on EKP power supply.
4.Switching on EKP for 3 minutes before start engine is suggested after empty tank. This can be written into instruction or operation manual. 
5.Detailed data should be verified on vehicle according to different EKP and LPC layout. Different EKP has different deflation capability.

Peak pressure measurement measurement (pump outlet)
1.Test is done for an preview of pump outlet Peak pressure measurement in LPV system. It is not able to demonstrate the potential and most critical pump outlet pressure.                                                                                                               2.Pump outlet pressure is 1800bar in critical working conditions in the system test on test bench. But we also need to consider the drift and sensitivity of RDS, Kistler sensor. Enough safety margin should be given in pump design.                                                                      
3.On vehicle test, pump peak outlet pressure can be higher than on test bench, especially in sudden acceleration and violent driving condition. Detail data should be collected through ETC LCM test.

Overpressure test
1.Test is done by simulating ZME failure in system running. Test is carried  out with CRI2.0 and CRI1.1 injectors, 2 Cylinder system is also taken into consideration.
2.System over pressure value with CRI1.1 is much higher than system with CRI2.0. System over pressure in system with EKP function is lower in amplitude shorter in last time than in system without EKP function.
3.System over pressure value in 3 cylinder system is lower than in 2 cylinder system because of different injector number which lead to different system leakage.                                                                                     4.System over pressure in LPV system is done with CRI2.0 and CRI1.1 injectors. Since CRI1-16 will be introduced into LPV platform, the system performance should be checked with it later.

QB calculation
1.CB08 W/O housing pump quantity balance is done at 80 degree keeping pump inlet pressure at 5.2bar(abs).
2.Pump flow rate at 80 degree is able to fulfill system requirement. But the age factor was not included in the test results.  A safety margin of 5% is considered to be decreased from the test results as the effect of age factor.

RPM verification
1.Rail pressure monitoring function is able to detect the leakage in high pressure circuit except in overrun condition. Additional monitoring function is needed to detect the high pressure leakage in overrun condition.
2.Rail pressure monitoring function is able to detect the leakage in low pressure circuit only when leakage is very huge and pressure before high pressure pump is extremely low.

Zero Delivery function verification

2.Zero delivery function of CB08 W/ housing works well until backflow pressure reaches 1.26bar.

Start ability test
CB08 W/ housing can start in about 1s even with pump speed @ 30prpm. System is able to start in around 0.5s @ pump speed higher than 50prpm.

LPC behavior (ZME leakage test)

2.Zero delivery function of CB08 W/ housing works well until backflow pressure reaches 1.26bar.                                                                    3.CB08 W/ housing can start in about 1s even with pump speed @ 30prpm. System is able to start in around 0.5s @ pump speed higher than 50prpm.
4.Supply pump control function is able to reduce the over pressure time but not the pressure peak when using CRI1-14 and CRI1-16 in system. Over pressure experiment should be repeated after CRI1-16 arrived in RBCD.
5.CRI1-16 injectors are going to be introduced into CRS1-16 system.

It’s also confirmed that CRI1-16 could not replace CRI2-16 just only with CRI1-16’s ET-map.

Fuel delivery rate and back pressure investigation for external backflow type
Current CB18 with external backflow LPC can’t fulfill system requirement if considering limit sample and aged factor influence.
In theory, it is possible to fulfill system requirement with 0.5bar inlet pressure specification if the targeted spill valve characteristic is strictly achieved.
If the actual limit sample and aged factor influence is bigger than that listed here, the above conclusion should be evaluated again.
6mm ID backflow pipe can’t be used for CB18 with external backflow.
Deflation ability is investigated by other colleague and not listed here

Fuel delivery rate and back pressure investigation for Partial external backflow type
CB18 partial external backflow can fulfill system requirement.

In start ability test, CB18 with partial external backflow shows weakness in critical conditions.

Zero delivery function test finds that CB18 with partial external backflow has problems even backflow pressure is only 1.15bar.

Deflation function of CB18 with partial external backflow is good. Air is not accumulated before vane pump. And no abnormal rail pressure behavior and engine shut off is detected.

Empty tank start up test shows that CB18 is difficult to start after fuel tank empty.

With modified OFV of partial external backflow: 
- Empty tank start ability: Rail pressure can be built up in about 5 seconds
-  Defloation: No air accumulation detected, no rail pressure fault detected, no engine shut off happen.
-

Partial external backflow:
- CB18 design change from inner backflow to partial external backflow has brought lots of advantages to CB18 pump. It owns good ventilation and empty tank start ability after design change.
- CB18 is much more robust than before in multi working conditions. Problems found in design change are all solved or being solved through improvements of design parameters. 
- The latest CB18 has been found problems in zero delivery function because of the modification of zero delivery circuit. Continuous improvements are going on.

Start ability: 
- Pump Start ability is influenced by backflow method and lobes especially in boundary conditions.
- Seeing from analysis result, in 70 ℃0m altitude 50prpm, start ability is mainly influenced by pressure after vane pump. CB18 inner backflow stronger in start ability.
- In 70 ℃0m altitude 75prpm, start ability is mainly influenced by lobes when pressure after vane pump is enough to open fuel inlet valve. CB18 OHW is stronger in start ability because it has 3 lobes

LPC verification:
CB18 OHW high pressure flow rate test shows that it is able to fulfill system requirement under the most critical working condition. Even considering 5% age factor and limit sample, there is still large safety margin left.
Start ability test result shows that CB18 OHW is comparable with CB18 On-High-Way in start ability.
Empty tank start test was repeated for 5 times and successful empty test start was achieved every time. Time for pump to build up rail pressure to 120bar was about 2-3 seconds.
Zero delivery function of CB18 On-High-Way has already been check, and the result was positive. Zero delivery function of CB18 OHW can be covered by CB18 On-High-Way since low pressure circuit of these two pumps are all the same. And CB18 OHW is even running in lower pump speed. 
System deflation ability test mainly focuses on low pressure circuit. It is also able to be covered by CB18 On-High-Way since test result of CB18 On-High-Way was positive.

LPC behavior measurement:
- 8mm ID pump inlet pipe is able to keep pressure drop less than 0.15bar in most critical low pressure layout and working condition.
- 6mm ID pump backflow pipe is able to keep backflow pressure under 1.1 bar in most critical low pressure layout and working condition.
- Test is done assuming fuel tank and pump in the same height.
- In the real vehicle, low pressure parameters are influenced by fuel tank position.
- If the engine is 1 meter higher than fuel tank, all the low pressure parameters should be decreased by 0.078bar.

Pump efficiency: CB18 OHW is able to fulfill system requirement in quantity balance. And its start ability is comparable with CB18 in test conditions
Empty tank start: Test done shows that CB18 OHW also owns good empty tank start ability.
Peak pressure measurement at injector inlet
Peak pressure measurement at injector inlet and pump outlet
Peak pressure measurement at injector inlet and pump outlet at system faiure mode

Over pressure test: Since there is risk at the time RDS or ZME failure when engine start, CB18 OHW pump running in low idle speed can't kick open PLV valve, system will remain running at low idle in a very high pressure (1850bar). This will harm the component in system especially high pressure pump.
Total possible error running time in life is calculated if assume DBV can only be open for 50 times, low idle(300prpm defined in system requirement) will remain 20 minutes at most for engine heating up after each start.
20minX50times=1000minutes=16.67 hours
Endurance tests should be arranged to verify the safety of system components under this circumstance.

LPC behavior measurement: ZP delivery rate is measured at different ZP back pressure, and the ZP back pressure is adjusted with a throttle from 2bar to 8 bar at different speed.

One problem has been found that when speed higher than 1100prpm, it’s hard to maintain ZP back pressure to certain value with the throttle.

Compared with ZP5 and ZP18.4, there are no pressure balance groove and pressure relieve groove in CB28’s ZP. Those may be the reason.

Peak pressure measurement measurement comparison: 
Peak pressure measurement at the pump outlet is increasing with the pump speed. Influence of pump speed at injector is relatively small.
Certain worst case area of Start of Energizing can be spotted

PRT has little impact on Peak pressure measurement at HPP and injector
PRT has little impact on delta pressure at injector
PRT does influence the delta pressure at the HPP

The maximum Peak pressure measurement at HPP is around 1736bar
Worst case delta pressure at HPP is 266bar without PRT
Worst case delta pressure at HPP is 193bar with PRT

Pump phasing investigation:
- 1.In this measurement, we investigated lots of working conditions covering all the potential points for the system with CB28
- 2.In the measurement, a whole range of camshaft angle is investigated to see the injection quantity change when changing the SOE, and there is a clear trend showing that in area 10 °to 50° injection quantity is very stable.
- 3.The comparison of the max and min value when changing the SOE shows it can be as high as 5mm^3 .
- An range of 10° to 50 ° can be primarily suggested in the A sample period, and this should be verified in all the period with the modification of the design of CB28 pump.

Zero Delivery function: In CB28, for 1,2bar suction valve opening pressure, the rail pressure is increasing for 1,2bar backflow pressure, the situation will be very critical when using 1.2bar suction valve opening pressure.

In CB28, for 1.4bar suction valve opening pressure, the rail pressure shows  no critical behavior with 1.28bar backflow pressure.

In order to prevent the DBV to be open in overrun condition, it is suggested to assure 1,4bar suction valve opening pressure at the end of lifetime for CB28.

In comparison, the CPN2.2 shows better performance in ZDT function. Even the backflow pressure is as high as 1.5bar, the rail pressure still shows very good behavior in overrun conditions.

The difference between CPN2.2 and CB28 in ZDT function reminds us that we should pay more attention to the ZDT function of CB28 especially in critical conditions, but the newly introduced guidance of suction valve spring to some extent ensures the ability of suction valve spring in the whole life time

LPC behavior measurement on VP outlet
n<700prpm, feed pump inlet pressure has oscillation;
n>700prpm, feed pump outlet pressure has big oscillation; max Peak pressure measurement is ~12.55bar@1400prpm; Peak to Peak pressure measurement ~10.37bar.
The oscillation frequency is the same as vane feeding frequency.

Big pressure oscillation at vane pump outlet will influence pipe lifetime.
Big pressure oscillation at vane pump outlet has a risk to burst main filter.

It has no problem to use this pump to check the start ability.

LPC behavior measurement The Peak pressure measurement and peak-to-Peak pressure measurement at CB28 vane pump outlet is too big compared with CPN2.2.
It’s hard to add over pressure valve to current vane pump to prevent main filter burst.
Risks can be seen:
Pipe disconnected or damaged
Blocked main filter burst and CRS damaged

Vane pump should be optimized and over pressure valve should be added.
Vane pump optimize suggestion:
Reduce the geometric volume and remove inlet throttle
Add special grooves at vane pump outlet

Mounting orientation: 
HP-pipe (ID and length) and injection control strategy (control Q or ET) have only little influence on the recommended mounting orientation.

The injection quantity deviation which caused by pump phasing is about 3% of the desired injection quantity at high load point.

If customer can follow certain mounting orientation, the injection quantity deviation (engine to engine) at high load will be below 1.5% of the desired injection quantity. 

Considering the possible MI and PI SOE range, the mounting orientation is recommended as that engine TDC should be 43±7°Cam angle before pump TDC.

If customer can not accept orientated mounting, ISP function can be used to decrease the impact of the pump phasing.

Injection deviation investigation
In this application, the max inj-q difference is about 2.5 mm^/str, which is happened at full load point. The difference of injection pressure correspondingly is about 74 bar.

The negative effect from emission side due to this difference should be evaluated by EVL.

The difference of injection quantity is possible to be reduced or even eliminated by ISP or FBC function (to be checked) but the difference of injection pressure can not be eliminated.

Start ability: 
With the use of EKP in CB08, the start ability of CB08 is comparable with CB18 in normal condition(40deg, 0m altitude).

CB08 is able to build up rail pressure to 120bar in 1s with pump speed of only 35prpm because of the EKP supplies constant pressure no matter how much the engine speed is.

With pump speed higher than 50prpm, CB08 is able to build up pressure to 120bar in about 0.5s.

Start ability of CB08 is estimated not so much influenced by high temperature and high altitude condition because of the use of EKP. Its flow rate is much higher than flow rate of VP and can be kept constant at start. But it will be checked again in further tests.

Empty tank start ability: 
Experiment is done with three different LPC layout methods: EKP in tank, EKP before filter and EKP after filter.

Experiment results are quite positive, with Rainbow EKP, system is able to start around 1 second. Because of the utilization of EKP, system deflation capability is out of a problem.

In system layout when EKP is after filter, air deflation after empty tank consumes 40 seconds in experiment. When low pressure pipe is very long, restart of engine should wait long engine after switching on EKP power supply.

Switching on EKP for 3 minutes before start engine is suggested after empty tank. This can be written into instruction or operation manual. 

Detailed data should be verified on vehicle according to different EKP and LPC layout. Different EKP has different deflation capability.

Peak pressure measurement of pump outlet: 
1.Test is done for an preview of pump outlet Peak pressure measurement in LPV system. It is not able to demonstrate the potential and most critical pump outlet pressure.                                                                                                               2.Pump outlet pressure is 1800bar in critical working conditions in the system test on test bench. But we also need to consider the drift and sensitivity of RDS, Kistler sensor. Enough safety margin should be given in pump design.                                                                      
3.On vehicle test, pump peak outlet pressure can be higher than on test bench, especially in sudden acceleration and violent driving condition. Detail data should be collected through ETC LCM test.

Over pressure test: 
1.Test is done by simulating ZME failure in system running. Test is carried  out with CRI2.0 and CRI1.1 injectors, 2 Cylinder system is also taken into consideration.
2.System over pressure value with CRI1.1 is much higher than system with CRI2.0. System over pressure in system with EKP function is lower in amplitude shorter in last time than in system without EKP function.
3.System over pressure value in 3 cylinder system is lower than in 2 cylinder system because of different injector number which lead to different system leakage.                                                                                     4.System over pressure in LPV system is done with CRI2.0 and CRI1.1 injectors. Since CRI1-16 will be introduced into LPV platform, the system performance should be checked with it later.

Rail pressure monitoring function: 
Rail pressure monitoring function is able to detect the leakage in high pressure circuit except in overrun condition. Additional monitoring function is needed to detect the high pressure leakage in overrun condition.
Rail pressure monitoring function is able to detect the leakage in low pressure circuit only when leakage is very huge and pressure before high pressure pump is extremely low.

Pump efficiency: 1.CB08 W/ housing is able to fulfill system requirement in all working conditions.
2.Zero delivery function of CB08 W/ housing works well until backflow pressure reaches 1.26bar.
Start ability: 3.CB08 W/ housing can start in about 1s even with pump speed @ 30prpm. System is able to start in around 0.5s @ pump speed higher than 50prpm.

Cold start ability:
Cold chamber start delay analysis:                                                                      1. Comparing all the data recorded in start process, no obvious differences were found.
2.Longer rail pressure build up time was caused by the loss of rail pressure build up in first two strokes.
3.With same fuel pressure before ZME in CB08, the loss of rail pressure build up in first two strokes could caused by air bubbles before I/O valve inside the high pressure pump.

1.For the different ET-map and SOI(SOE), CRI1-16 could not replace CRI2-16 directly without any adjustment, then EVL would do some test with CRI1-16 ET-MAP to check the running change in the engine bed.

It’s explained why CRI2-16 and CRI1-16 have different behaviour in the engine bench, when the pilot injection be applied.
It’s also confirmed that CRI1-16 could not replace CRI2-16 just only with CRI1-16’s ET-map.
